&lt;h2&gt;About the team&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Avride is a rapidly developing company in the autonomous vehicle and delivery robot industry. We develop autonomous vehicle technology from scratch, leveraging the strong technical background of our core team and over seven years of experience in autonomous vehicle development. Our Finance team collaborates closely with cross-functional partners to drive financial excellence and supports critical business decisions across global operations. Join us and contribute to a high-impact team where your expertise will help shape Avride’s financial future.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a detail-oriented and reliable Accountant to support our U.S.&amp;nbsp;finance operations. This role will be responsible for reviewing expense reports, maintaining accounts payable and fixed assets as well as&lt;br&gt;supporting day-to-day accounting and reconciliation activities. This roll will be integral to the month end close process. The ideal candidate will have 3-5 years of experience with accounting, and a proactive, hands-on approach to daily operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accounting Operations:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with day-to-day accounting operations, including journal entries, prepaid transactions, and month-end close tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for accounts payable, expensify, and fixed assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support AP reconciliations and the AP run process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor GL accounts and resolve discrepancies in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Process Improvement &amp;amp; Compliance:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure adherence to internal controls over AP and fixed asset accounting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and propose improvements to streamline processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in preparing documentation for internal and external audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll need&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years of general accounting experience, preferably in a U.S. GAAP based company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with NetSuite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Excel skills and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Nice to have&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to cost accounting or expense allocation practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of equity or bonus compensation accounting is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-MS1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em class=&quot;italic-text&quot;&gt;Candidates are required to be authorized to work in the U.S. The employer is not offering relocation sponsorship, and remote work options are not available.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em class=&quot;italic-text&quot;&gt;Avride is an equal opportunity employer and committed to providing reasonable accommodations to qualified applicants and employees with disabilities to ensure they have equal access to employment opportunities. Avride complies with the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA), if you need a reasonable accommodation to assist with the application or hiring process, or to perform the essential functions of a job, please email &lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:jobs@avride.ai&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;jobs@avride.ai&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Avride, we’re tackling one of the most complex challenges humanity has ever faced—creating autonomous vehicles and delivery robots that redefine the future of mobility. Our work goes beyond innovation.&amp;nbsp; It’s about transforming everyday life, making it more efficient, sustainable, and connected. We’re home to some of the brightest and most talented minds in the industry, offering you an unparalleled opportunity to learn, grow, and collaborate with experts across diverse fields. With a our delivery robots, already in the market, you can witness firsthand how our technology is changing the world, one delivery at a time. If you’re passionate about innovation and eager to be part of a team that’s shaping the future, Avride is the place for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Account Manager on our Delivery Robot team, you&#39;ll oversee a portfolio of university partners and ensure our delivery robot program exceeds campus expectations. You&#39;ll serve as the voice of the university — surfacing their questions, feedback, and evolving needs internally so the customer perspective is always represented. You&#39;ll also collaborate with the broader Commercial team to identify growth opportunities and bring those possibilities to life with campus partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of Avride’s products and services, including our features, benefits, and value propositions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in managing a portfolio of campus accounts, ensuring timely communication, and resolving inquiries and concerns with care and urgency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist and partner with campuses to drive delivery demand and deliver and exceptional experience for their dining communities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular check-ins with campus partners to gather feedback, assess satisfaction levels, and identify areas for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to all campus inquiries, account issues, and requests or route them to appropriate company departments within turnaround time expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of client interactions, including discussion notes, action items, and follow-up tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in training sessions and workshops to enhance product knowledge, sales skills, and overall proficiency in account management practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively seek opportunities to contribute to team goals and initiatives, demonstrating a willingness to learn and grow in the role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 18pt;&quot;&gt;What you’ll need&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree or High School degree/GED with&amp;nbsp;equivalent professional experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of Sales or Account Manager experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency with Google products and Slack along with the ability to quickly learn new software. Experience with Google Sheets and Salesforce&amp;nbsp;is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Native-level fluency in English is required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine drive to go above and beyond to find solutions for university partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidence engaging with University leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A responsive, always-on mindset. You treat your campus partners like true partners, and they know they can count on you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of success in meeting and exceeding goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate with confidence in ambiguous, fast-moving situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Impeccable organizational skills, easily

&lt;h2&gt;About the team&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Avride is a rapidly developing company in the autonomous vehicle and delivery robot industry. We develop autonomous vehicle technology from scratch, leveraging the strong technical background of our core team and over seven years of experience in autonomous vehicle development. Our Recruiting team collaborates closely with cross-functional partners to identify top talent and drive our growth. Join us and contribute to a high-impact team where your expertise will help shape Avride’s future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Avride is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Contract Talent Partner/Junior Recruiter&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to fuel our rapidly growing workforce. In this pivotal role, you will own the full-cycle recruitment process for our hourly contract teams, ensuring we scale with both speed and precision. As the primary point of contact for candidates, you’ll partner closely with hiring managers to identify top talent and accelerate the hiring funnel while maintaining the high-standard candidate experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full lifecycle recruiting for our hourly contractor workforce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct high volume phone/video screens daily to identify and qualify talent for hourly roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the face of Avride, moving candidates through the funnel with speed, clarity, and genuine enthusiasm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and manage recruiting logistics including scheduling onsites, prepping candidates for success, and following up to keep candidates engaged.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiate background check and other pre-employment steps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate offers and start dates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and attend hiring events, networking functions and career fairs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the broader recruiting team to meet corporate hiring goals and objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll need&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 2-3 years of recruiting or staffing experience in an agency or in-house environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with high-volume/hourly hiring (ops, drivers, warehouse, trades, support, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to deliver a great candidate experience at scale - clear communication, respect, and responsiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organization and fast paced - nothing slips thru the cracks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable being on calls all day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can quickly understand the value our company offers and position the company and role in a compelling way to candidates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with an ATS or agency CRM, such as Greenhouse, and familiarity with tools like Slack and Google Workspace.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General HR knowledge and a solid understanding of employment law/compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Nice to have&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for autonomous vehicles and technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of local labor laws and background check nuances&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with creative sourcing to find candidates in non-traditional places&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em class=&quot;italic-text&quot;&gt;Candidates are required to be authorized to work in the U.S. The employer is not offering relocation sponsorship, and remote work options are not available.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
