&lt;h2&gt;About us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Avride is autonomous driving technology. We&#39;re building two products simultaneously: a robotaxi for passenger transportation and delivery robots for last-mile logistics. Both are already operating on city streets — not in test mode, but in real-world deployment. We&#39;re a small, focused team — no unnecessary approval layers or diffused ownership. There are complex challenges, fast decisions, and a product people can see in person.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Senior Brand Designer to build and evolve Avride&#39;s visual language — from strategic decisions to hands-on execution. This is one of the first dedicated brand roles at the company, so you&#39;ll have real influence over how Avride looks and feels. You&#39;ll work closely with marketing, product, and leadership — translating a technically complex subject into clear, compelling, and visually strong communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain Avride&#39;s visual identity — from brand guidelines to specific applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design materials for marketing, PR, events, partner presentations, and B2B communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set and uphold design standards across all touchpoints — digital, print, and physical&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to campaign concepting and visual storytelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate external contractors and agencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who we&#39;re looking for&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of professional brand design experience in a commercial environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong portfolio featuring comprehensive brand identity work — not just individual mockups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with design systems and brand guidelines — you know how to create the rules and ensure they&#39;re followed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Figma and Adobe Creative Suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in typography, visual systems, conceptual thinking, and storytelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort operating autonomously in a small team — no hand-holding, no waiting for perfect briefs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong English — written and spoken; we work in an international environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Nice to have&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience at early-stage startups where a brand was built or rebuilt from scratch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with technically complex products — robotics, automotive, hardware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3D skills for creating visually compelling content and bringing ideas to life through dynamic imagery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What we offer&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on a product that physically exists in the world and continues to scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Influence over the company&#39;s visual identity from day one&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A small team where you don&#39;t need to wait for permission to try something new&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
